Ability: Intelligence.Requires Training: No.Classes: All.The higher the character's skill the better the price received when selling or purchasing goods.Check: The character makes an opposed roll against the merchant's Appraise skill. If the merchant wins, the characters pay more for the goods in the store. If the character wins, they pay less. The first time the player interacts with a merchant dictates the prices in that store until their Appraise skill improves.Use: Automatic in stores.